NAME
       unlx - extract a specific file from an lx archive via stdin

SYNOPSIS
       unlx <filename>

DESCRIPTION
       unlx reads an lx-formatted archive from standard input and extracts 
       the contents of the specified <filename> to standard output.

       The script parses the archive by looking for metadata markers in the 
       form of `# file <filename>` followed by a code block delimited by 
       triple backticks (```). When a match is found, the content within 
       the subsequent code block is printed.

OPTIONS
       <filename>
              The exact name of the file to be extracted from the archive.

EXIT STATUS
       0      Success.

       1      An error occurred (e.g., no filename was provided as an 
              argument). A usage message is printed to stderr.

EXAMPLES
       Extracting 'config.json' from a local lx archive:
             cat archive.lx | unlx config.json

       Redirecting the output to a file:
             unlx script.py < archive.lx > script.py

NOTES
       The utility expects input in the following format:
       # file filename_here
       ```
       content...
       ```

